Date:         Thu, 28 Jul 88 16:07:35 EDT
Reply-To:     Virus Discussion List <VIRUS-L@LEHIIBM1>
Sender:       Virus Discussion List <VIRUS-L@LEHIIBM1>
From:         Loren K Keim   -- Lehigh University <LKK0@LEHIGH>

(Heavy mail is BACK on Virus-L!)

One more thing Neil,

We're more and more referring to Anti-Viral programs as
"Virus Detection Systems" not "Virus Prevention".  The object
t is to detect the virus as early as possible.  You can't stop
that first infection (primary infection) from someone elses
system, but you may be able to stop it from infecting a
second file, or from actually doing damage to your system.

We're relagate d to fighting the symptons rather than the fi
viruses themselves.

Loren
