Subject:      How many viruses are there?

Agreed, I didn't mean to be trying to pin you down to a specific
number.   I was just surprised to hear a number as high as 70;
I guess a lot more has been going on than anyone has mentioned
here or in similar places.   I'll be eagerly awaiting your posting
of your list!

I think the point about people using lots of different
anti-viral programs is a very good one; this is one field where
you don't want your own program to be the One Everyone Uses,
because if it is, the virus-writers will target it, take it
apart, and design circumventions.   Safety in Numbers!

DC
